.TH QEMUCONF 1 "January 2023" "qemuconf @VERSION@"

.SH NAME
qemuconf \- simple qemu launcher with config file support

.SH SYNOPSIS
.P
\fBqemuconf\fR [\fB-q\fR \fIEXEC\fR] \fICONFIG\fR [-- QEMU ARGS ...]
.P
\fBqemuconf\fR [\fB-n\fR] \fICONFIG\fR
.P
\fBqemuconf\fR [\fB-V\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qemuconf
executes
.BR qemu (1)
with arguments compiled from a configuration file.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-q\fR \fIEXEC\fR
Set the default \fBqemu\fR binary.  This option may be overwritten by
the \fIbinary\fR option in the configuration file.
.TP
\fB-n\fR \fICONFIG\fR
Print the produced argument list to stdout, instead of executing.
Useful for diagnostic purposes.
.TP
.B -V
Print version and exit.

.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
#
# /etc/qemuconf.d/generic.conf: configuration file for qemuconf(1)
#

binary  /usr/bin/qemu-system-x86_64
cwd     /var/qemu/generic
smp     2
m       1024
enable-kvm
drive:
  if      virtio
  file    hda.img
net nic:
  vlan    0
  model   virtio
  macaddr 82:82:9D:AF:F0:1C
net user:
  vlan    0
vnc 127.0.0.1:1

# End of file.
.fi
.P
The configuration file will execute the following command:
.nf
/usr/bin/qemu-system-x86_64 -smp 2 -m 1024 -enable-kvm \\
  -drive if=virtio,file=hda.img \\
  -net nic,vlan=0,model=virtio,macaddr=82:82:9D:AF:F0:1C \\
  -net user,vlan=0 \\
  -vnc 127.0.0.1:1
.fi
.P
The "cwd" option instructs \fBqemuconf\fR to
.BR chdir (2)
into \fI/var/qemu/generic\fR before executing a
.BR qemu (1)
instance.

.SH DIAGNOSTICS
To show the produced arguments list use the following:
.P
.nf
    ~ $ qemuconf -n config.conf
.fi

